You are adding an element to the list after getting the iterator. That iterator is no longer available. Using that iterator will result in the exception `ConcurrentModificationException`. You have to get the iterator after adding all the elements.  You should change `printCustomer()` like this.

    public static void printCustomer() {
        Iterator&lt;customer&gt; iterate = customers.iterator();
        while (iterate.hasNext()) {
            customer element = iterate.next();
            System.out.println(customers.indexOf(element));
        }
    }

